Title: The electrically charged BTZ black hole with self(anti-self) dual

Maxwell fieldAuthors: Masaru Kamata and Takao Koikawa

Comments: 7 pages, no figs

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B353 (1995) 196-200

The Einstein-Maxwell equations with a negative cosmological constant in 2+1spacetime dimensions discussed by Banados, Teitelboim and Zanelli are solved byassuming a self(anti-self)dual equation. The solution describes an electricallycharged extreme black hole with an angular momentum.